Ken,

That's not true, Positron is based on Electron 34 which supports macOS 11 just fine (as do all stable releases of Electron). The breakage comes from the Jupyter R kernel which ostensibly was intended to be backward compatible (with minos set to 10.12 which is ancient) so it looks like an oversight at build time more than an intention. That is not to say that reliance on such a long list of 3rd party code doesn't have problems in that regard, so I wouldn?t hold my breath (Electron did announce the intent to break it in the future releases).

Cheers,
Simon


